{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a handoff/sequencing failure across manifest validation + loader execution boundary, not just a single-function parse check (MOCK-MISS). No real network/subprocess/external contract round-trip is required, so System is rejected. No AI dependency.","test_description":"Create a test plugin on disk with an invalid manifest and an entry module that writes a sentinel file or flips shared state on import. Run the real loader over the plugin directory and assert: (1) rejection error identifies missing field, (2) sentinel side effect never occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's onLoad hook is called before plugin A's.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Requires multiple modules wired together: dependency graph resolution + lifecycle executor ordering. Unit-only checks of topo-sort or hook runner separately can miss integration ordering bugs. System rejected because behavior text does not require external contract/round-trip beyond in-process loader execution.","test_description":"Set up two plugins in a temp plugin directory where A depends on B; each onLoad appends its name to a shared in-memory/event log. Execute loader and assert call order is [B, A].","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.88,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection + load suppression is an orchestration behavior across manifest parsing, graph build, and load executor. Unit tests of cycle detection alone can miss that loader still imports/loads accidentally. System rejected: no explicit external API/HTTP/subprocess contract needed.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies and onLoad side-effect sentinels. Run loader and assert: (1) cycle error is reported with both plugin names, (2) neither plugin is imported/onLoad-called (no sentinel side effects).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's onLoad hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is explicit sequencing between module import side effects and hook invocation across loader/runtime boundaries. A pure unit mock of import can hide ordering bugs; integration with real local modules provides the needed signal. System rejected because no external boundary contract/round-trip is specified.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets a global/module flag during import; onLoad asserts that flag is already set and records success. Run loader and assert onLoad runs only after import side effect has occurred.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its onLoad hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Needs integrated behavior of dependency filtering + failure isolation + continuation semantics across multiple plugins. Unit tests of error handling in isolation may miss graph-aware continuation behavior. System rejected due no required external contract/readback beyond local loader state.","test_description":"Define plugins: F (throws in onLoad), D (depends on F), and C (independent). Run loader and assert: F fails, D is skipped/not loaded due dependency, C still initializes successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.89,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
